President Barack Obama has declared May 2016 as Older Americans Month in the United States. In his proclamation, he highlights the valuable contributions that older Americans have made to the country and emphasizes the need to support and empower them. Obama mentions the importance of programs like Medicare and Social Security in ensuring the stability and security of older Americans. He also discusses initiatives launched by his administration, such as the myRA savings bond and the reauthorization of the Older Americans Act, which provide support for seniors' health, independence, and retirement. Obama calls on Americans of all ages to celebrate and honor older Americans and their contributions.